# Bearer rule IDs skipped for the ai-protect self-scan. Honored by the bearer
# adapter via --skip-rule.
# ai-protect is a security-tool ORCHESTRATOR: ~40 adapters shell out to their
# CLI (nuclei, trufflehog, semgrep, ...) with list-form argv (no shell), so
# bearer's command-injection rule fires categorically. There is no shell=True
# anywhere (confirmed by bandit), and inputs are validated. The signal-bearing
# bearer rules (path traversal, weak crypto, etc.) remain enabled.
python_lang_os_command_injection
